<TEXT>
in a tiny seaside village police on 
wednesday fatally wounded a gunman they said killed at least 11 
people in a shooting rampage that was new zealands worst massacre 
officials said 
police said 33yearold david malcolm gray who had fled to a 
house on the villages northern edge after being driven from his 
own had been shot in the chest and ankle and also suffered a head 
wound 
at about 545 pm police lobbed smoke grenades into the house 
and stormed it ending a 21hour ordeal that wiped out nearly half 
the population of the village of aramoana 
blackclad officers some with ski masks had stormed grays 
house nearly two hours earlier but found it empty and began a 
search 
police originally said gray was being airlifted by army 
helicopter to nearby dunedin later they said he had died of his 
injuries 
aramoana which had a population of 25 before the rampage is 
about 17 miles north of dunedin in rugged country on new zealands 
south island 
victims of the massacre included a 6yearold boy who had rode 
his bicycle up to the gunmans house to see what was happening and 
a police sergeant from nearby port chalmers whose body was found in 
dunes outside of town 
bodies lay strewn about outside grays house and a neighboring 
home that he had set on fire when the rampage began tuesday night 
said dunedin police sgt bill obrien 
police had been unable to check if the victims were still alive 
for fear the gunman might open fire gray had been holed up inside 
his home for much of wednesday firing indiscriminately they said 
about 140 police including an antiterrorism squad had poured 
into remote aramoana after the shooting began 
police spokeswoman kaye calder said police found a 22caliber 
rifle an air rifle and 9mm ammunition inside grays home 
residents who had been trapped in their homes since the 
onslaught began were finally evacuated aboard a navy training 
vessel the hmnzs moa 
they had spent a terrifying night huddled on the floors of their 
homes as gunfire punctuated the silence 
the worst previous worst massacre in new zealand occurred in 
1941 when eric stanley graham killed six police officers before 
being shot dead 
the rampage started tuesday evening when gray who apparently 
lived alone set his neighbors house on fire and began shooting at 
firemen and residents who approached to put it out according to 
neighbors 
obrien said police were mystified as to what sparked the 
incident 
we dont know why he has done this he said 
aramoana is among cliffs and sandy marshes in an isolated area 
across otago harbor from taiaroa head a famous albatross colony 
that attracts birders from around the world 
dorothy crimp 74 who lives across from grays house described 
him as a very quiet chap a real loner 
i have met him on the beach he never spoke to anyone 
