imminent 
the united states is seeking to eliminate 75 percent of current 
domestic farm supports and import barriers and to reduce export 
subsidies by 90 percent 
the european community with its network of heavily subsidized 
small family farms has labeled the bush proposal politically 
unrealistic the ec wants to trim 30 percent of 1986 farm supports 
which the united states says would be only a 15 percent cut from 
current subsidies while leaving the import barriers and export 
subsidies untouched 
the farm issue is considered central to completion of the 
current round of global trade talks which involve 105 nations 
under the auspices of the general agreement on tariffs and trade 
thousands of farmers from france germany italy and switzerland 
