offices and makeshift evacuation centers president corazon aquino 
who returned wednesday from japan declared 30 of the countrys 73 
provinces disaster areas 
unconfirmed radio reports put the death toll at about 30 in 
cebu a city of more than a half million people and the countrys 
second most important transport and industrial center after manila 
telephone lines to the city were cut and residents reached by 
radio from manila 350 miles to the north said hundreds of 
buildings were damaged and the city was without electricity 
nineteen ships sank in the storm including 17 in cebu harbor 
