<TEXT>
single men looking for a raise or 
promotion should consider a serious option get married 
married men earn an average of 306 percent more than unmarried 
men according to a university of michigan survey released tuesday 
husbands outearn bachelors in several other countries as well 
said robert schoeni a doctoral student at the schools population 
studies center 
the average earnings of married men were consistently higher 
than the earnings of their unmarried counterparts in all the 
countries we studied the effect persisted even when education age 
or experience and race were taken into account schoeni said 
he offered three possible explanations 
employers are more likely to hire and promote married men 
because they consider them more stable and community oriented 
women are more likely to marry financially successful men 
married men feel responsible for a wife and family and become 
more productive 
our data doesnt clarify which is the correct explanation i 
suspect however that all three explanations play a role 
schoeni said 
schoeni studied incomes in 12 countries using data for 25 to 
64yearold males collected since 1983 by the center for 
population poverty and policy studies in walferdange luxembourg 
he said he found marriage had a particularly powerful effect on 
mens earnings in the united states norway sweden and 
switzerland 
in the united states the effect was powerful at all ages 288 
percent at age 30 303 percent at age 40 and 325 percent at age 
50 
in italy and in predemocracy poland the effect was weaker 
93 percent in italy and only 31 percent in poland schoeni said 
he didnt know why the gap was narrower in italy he said a planned 
economy like predemocracy polands was not affected much by issues 
such as marriage 
the gap in different countries 
australia 136 percent 
canada 144 percent 
france 127 percent 
germany 124 percent 
italy 93 percent 
netherlands 119 percent 
norway 264 percent 
poland 31 percent 
sweden 261 percent 
switzerland 259 percent 
united kingdom 127 percent 
united states 306 percent 
