<TEXT>
the 1973 war powers act requires that the 
president consult with congress formally when us forces are 
introduced into hostilities or into situations where imminent 
involvement in hostilities is clearly indicated by the 
circumstances 
notification also is required when combatequipped troops are 
sent to the territory of any foreign nation 
the notification must include the presidents explanation of why 
the move is necessary and the estimated scope and duration of the 
deployment 
the law requires that the president terminate the military 
deployment within 60 days unless congress has specifically 
authorized its continuation the 60day period can be extended to 
90 days if the president certifies that such a move is an 
unavoidable military necessity 
administrations regard the act as an unconstitutional 
infringement by congress on the presidents powers as 
commanderinchief of the armed forces rather than tackle the 
issue headon however notification usually is given in a way that 
congress regards as compliance with the law 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

