<TEXT>
here are key events in the history of eastern airlines over the 
past 15 years 
1975 frank borman former astronaut becomes president 
1976 borman becomes chairman and wins pay freeze from workers 
1978 congress deregulates airline industry allowing carriers 
to set their own fares and fly where they want as fare wars begin 
borman plunges eastern deep into debt by buying a fleet of new 
planes 
1980 easterns debt swells to more than 22 billion 
1983 borman threatens to take eastern into bankruptcy without 
concessions from employees to reduce costs they relent in exchange 
for a 25 percent stake in the company and seats on the board 
1985 labor tension increases despite union participation in 
running the company eastern barely breaks even due to fare wars 
1986 easterns debt increases to 25 billion company again 
considers bankruptcy lays off more than 1000 workers and gets 
wage concessions from pilots but debt pressure forces the sale of 
the airline to texas air corp for 676 million borman quits 
1987 texas air boss frank lorenzo considered a unionbuster 
by organized labor vows to cut costs at eastern 
march 1989 lorenzo rejects union demands workers strike and 
eastern seeks protection from creditors in bankruptcy court 
lorenzo replaces strikers and sells some eastern assets notably 
the northeast shuttle to developer donald trump 
april 1989 an attempt to buy eastern led by former baseball 
commissioner peter ueberroth collapses eastern vows to reorganize 
into a smaller airline 
september 1989 lorenzo predicts eastern will turn a profit in 
1990 
november 1989 striking pilots and flight attendants vote to 
return to work leaving machinists alone on picket lines 
december 1989 american airlines agrees to buy easterns latin 
american routes for 471 million shrinking eastern by about 
onethird 
january 1990 eastern backs away from earlier pledge to fully 
repay all its debts 
march 1990 special examiner in bankruptcy case finds texas air 
victimized eastern by purchasing some key assets at unfairly low 
prices texas air disputes the report but agrees to give eastern 
280 million in compensation 
april 1990 angry creditors frustrated by easterns rising 
losses and reduced plan for repayment seek appointment of a 
special trustee to run the airline and possibly find a buyer 
bankruptcy judge burton lifland grants their request seizing 
control from lorenzo and appoints veteran airline executive martin 
r shugrue jr to run the airline 
may 1990 shugrue launches a 100 days promotional campaign 
vowing to make eastern profitable and woo back passengers he 
follows in september with a plan for targeting business travelers 
november 1990 shugrues estimates for recovery prove grossly 
optimistic partly because of an economic downturn and rapidly 
rising fuel costs caused by the persian gulf crisis exasperated 
creditors decide to seek liquidation of the airline 
