<TEXT>
the food and drug administration took action 
wednesday aimed at making it harder for generic drug companies to 
cheat on tests needed to win agency approval for their products 
the fda said it has begun requiring all testing laboratories to 
retain for five years samples of drugs tested to ensure that 
generics are substantially the same as the brand name drug from 
which they are copied 
currently the labs are not required to retain samples 
in some previous instances of cheating generic drug companies 
have substituted a brandname drug for their own in tests to 
determine whether the two versions act the same in the body 
in these instances where products were switched the brand name 
drug was compared with itself rather than with the product to be 
approved 
the agency said the samples that now have to be retained can be 
used as evidence in investigations into wrongdoing 
the requirement applies to all drug products whether generic or 
brand name that are tested for equivalence of action 
genberic drugs are sold by companies who manufacture them after 
the patent on the brandname equivalent has expired 
