identities or further details 
iraq has been releasing scores of western hostages in recent 
weeks including some who have been held as human shields at 
strategic installations to deter a possible attack 
bushs meeting with lawmakers came against a backdrop of growing 
congressional concern about the scope of us military involvement 
in the gulf the president announced last week that 200000 new 
us troops would be sent to provide an offensive military 
option for use against iraq that will nearly double us troop 
strength in the region now at about 230000 
senate majority leader george mitchell said after talking with 
bush that the buildup is not in and of itself a decision to use 
force but rather is intended to create credible options 
democratic leaders told bush they believe the constitution would 
require him to seek congressional authorization before using 
military force in the gulf secretary of state james a baker iii 
said bush would follow the constitution but added that there 
was some question about its interpretation 
