france tested a nuclear weapon wednesday in the 
south pacific and publicly announced the explosion in keeping with 
a new policy new zealand quickly condemned the test 
the french defense ministry said a device with explosive power 
below 100 kilotons was detonated at fangataufa in french polynesia 
one kiloton has the explosive force of 1000 tons of tnt 
over the previous 15 years france had refused to comment on its 
nuclear tests in the south pacific word of such tests came from an 
observation station operated by new zealand in the cook islands 
in may president francois mitterrand announced during a trip to 
the south pacific that france would begin announcing the tests 
which many countries in the region oppose french officials also 
said the number of tests would be reduced from eight to six 
annually 
wednesdays test was the fifth under the new disclosure policy 
