the struggle for control of the southern baptist convention 
moved to the states this week as moderates and conservatives vied 
for leadership and grappled with mission spending and control of 
colleges 
moderate members of the nations largest protestant denomination 
appeared wednesday to continue their historic domination of state 
conventions fundamentalists hold sway at the national level 
moderates have contended in recent years they have been stripped 
of a voice because the conservativecontrolled national convention 
decides which missions seminaries and other programs get sbc 
funds 
by maintaining control at the state level moderates say they 
are able to have at least some pull in how funds are spent even 
though the state and national conventions operate autonomously 
conservatives have taken over the national convention because 
of the deceit that says there is liberalism among moderates 
said the rev bill sherman pastor of nashvilles woodmont baptist 
church and a moderate leader 
