the personal computer of 1995 will recognize 
its owners handwriting and voice and display crystal clear 3d 
images on a thin flat screen computer experts predict 
it also will be smaller and lighter than todays machines in 
fact it may be so portable it may be carried by users everywhere 
they go much like an appointment book a panel of indusry 
officials predicted tuesday at the weeklong comdex computer show 
in addition the 1995 models will be in constant contact with 
the rest of the world through builtin cellular phone or radio 
hookups enabling them to send and receive messages as well as news 
reports faxes and documents 
in case that sounds like a delirious dream consider how far 
