cs first boston inc will lay off about 200 
workers by the end of the year and surrender majority ownership to 
the parent of credit swisse in a major rescue effort for the 
struggling investment bank 
first boston will sell 300 million in equity to cs holding 
raising the swiss companys stake to 60 percent from 445 percent 
also cs will give cs first boston 425 million in cash for the 
bulk of its troubled loan portfolio the weak loans have weighed 
heavily on its balance sheet and led to a potentially damaging 
credit rating review 
the rescue is the latest fallout from wall streets lingering 
recession that has eliminated tens of thousands of jobs dried up 
profitable business sectors and forced major firms to seek help 
from corporate parents 
the deal also marks the first time a foreign company has taken 
majority control of a major us investment bank cs first boston 
is the parent of first boston corp which had about 3850 
employees at the end of october 
we want to be certain that the depth of our commitment to cs 
first boston is clear and that the strength of our investment 
banking affiliate is beyond question cs holding chairman rainer 
s gut said in a statement 
the bailout by cs holding is the second this year by the parent 
of an ailing wall street subsidiary american express co early 
this year injected 13 billion into shearson lehman holdings inc 
and took the company private 
the first boston restructuring rids the firm of the majority of 
11 billion in temporary bridge loans made to corporate 
clients that the firm has been unable to sell because of the 
collapse of the junk bond market 
under the plan cs first boston will place all its bridge loans 
except for those to campeau corps federated department stores 
subsidiary and to jerrico inc into a special limited partnership 
in exchange cs first boston will receive a stake in the 
partnership which also will contain some equity investments and 
the 425 million in cash the firm still will hold 377 million in 
the troublesome bridge loans however 
additionally cs first boston announced it was writing off 360 
million in soured investments including the federated and jerrico 
bridge loans and some real estate venture capital and leveraged 
buyout investments 
that action is expected to reduce the firms 1990 earnings 
first boston made just 11 million last year and reportedly has 
losses so far this year 
wall street analysts said the moves were favorable and could 
head off a potential downgrade in first bostons credit rating 
which would make the firms daily borrowing requirements more 
costly 
the closer relationship with cs holding and the strenghtening 
of the financial structure are positive steps said john j kriz 
a vice president with moodys investors service inc a major 
credit rating agency 
moodys several weeks ago placed first bostons credit rating 
under review kriz said moodys would evaluate the rating in light 
of the recapitalization plan 
the 200 layoffs are in addition to about 100 firings in recent 
weeks in the firms stock and operations departments by the end of 
the year first boston will have reduced its total us employment 
by nearly 8 percent the company employs 5800 people worldwide 
the firm was taken private in 1988 in a merger between first 
boston and its european affiliate but it fell on hard times last 
year particularly because of the collapse in the market for junk 
bonds the highyield securities in which the company was a major 
player 
